<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900709-0054</DOCNO><DOCID>900709-0054.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   Pittston Co. Names   Farrell as President   And Operating Chief</HL><DATE>07/09/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7</SO><CO>   WNEWS PCO</CO><IN>COAL PRODUCERS (COA)</IN><LP>   GREENWICH, Conn. -- Pittston Co. named Joseph C. Farrellto the new position of president and chief operating officer,making him the odds -- on choice to succeed chief executivePaul W. Douglas when he retires next year.   The 63-year-old Mr. Douglas, who is scheduled to step downin September 1991, said the promotions of Mr. Farrell, 54,and David L. Marshall, 51, who was named to the new post ofvice chairman, would make for an &quot;orderly process oftransition.&quot;</LP><TEXT>   Messrs. Farrell and Marshall were previously executivevice presidents.   Mr. Douglas became chief executive of Pittston in 1984with the charge of streamlining the then-troubled coal miningand transport concern. He has largely succeeded, though notwithout suffering a nine-month coal miners' strike that endedin January. Mr. Farrell was the company's chief negotiator inthe contract talks with the United Mine Workers union.   In addition to the promotions, Pittston said it formed anew, four-man office of the chairman, consisting of Messrs.Douglas, Farrell and Marshall and Robert D. Duke, senior vicepresident and general counsel.</TEXT></DOC>